Looking at the code differences, the main issue is that the Rust implementation isn't truly parallelizing all downloads - it processes each page of blob listings sequentially and only parallelizes within each page. Also, it's creating a new HTTP client for each request.

Here's an optimized version that properly parallelizes all downloads using a semaphore to control concurrency (similar to C#'s `MaxDegreeOfParallelism`) and reuses the HTTP client.

